'''Jacob Michael Italiano''' (born 30 July 2001)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.perthglory.com.au/player/jacob-italiano|title=Jacob Italiano|website=Perth Glory FC|language=en|access-date=6 June 2019}}</ref> is an Australian professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[right back]] for Austrian [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] club [[Grazer AK]] and the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]].

He has previously played for Australian club [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]] and German club [[Borussia Mönchengladbach II]].

==Club career==
===Perth Glory===
{{Expand section|date=October 2025}}

===Borussia Mönchengladbach===
In May 2019, Italiano moved to German club [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/a-league/teams/perth-glory/jacob-italiano-borussia-monchengladbach-move-teen-to-move-to-germany-in-2019/news-story/09fc6fbaf515463074f7419ebf6665ce|title=Jacob Italiano, Borussia Monchengladbach move|date=13 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.perthglory.com.au/news/trio-depart-club-0|title=Trio depart club|website=Perth Glory FC|date=23 May 2019|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref> He played for the [[Borussia Mönchengladbach II|reserves side]] and often trained with the senior team.

===Grazer AK===
In June 2024, Italiano joined newly promoted Austrian club [[Grazer AK]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://grazerak.at/aktuelles/saison-24-25-herzlich-willkommen-jacob-italiano|title= Herzlich Willkommen, Jacob Italiano – oder: He comes from a land down under |trans-title=Welcome, Jacob Italiano – or: He comes from a land down under
|language=de|website=[[Grazer AK]]|date=18 June 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Australia, Italiano is dual-citizen of Australia and Italy.<ref name="bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website 2001">{{cite web | title=Jacob Michael Italiano - Borussia M'gladbach - Player Profile | website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website | date=30 July 2001 | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/jacob-italiano | access-date=5 June 2023}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australian national team]] for a set of friendlies in October 2025, making his debut against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://socceroos.com.au/news/eight-commbank-socceroos-changes-canada-usa-matches|title=Eight CommBank Socceroos changes for Canada, USA matches|website=[[Australia men's national soccer team|Socceroos]]|publisher=[[Football Australia]]|date=3 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://socceroos.com.au/news/commbank-socceroos-squad-update-october|title=CommBank Socceroos Squad Update|website=[[Australia men's national soccer team|Socceroos]]|publisher=[[Football Australia]]|date=5 October 2025}}</ref>

